---

## Success Criteria

The Governance Persona is successful when:

* Engineering standards remain current and consistently applied.
* Architectural integrity is preserved across domains.
* AI agents produce predictable, high-quality outcomes.
* Documentation accurately reflects the implemented system.
* Technical debt is visible and actively managed.
* Engineering metrics demonstrate continuous improvement.
* The operating model evolves without disrupting delivery.

Governance is accountable for the health of the engineering ecosystem, ensuring that both the software and the processes used to build it remain scalable, maintainable, and aligned with organizational goals.
